DefaultDialogue: Reekwater is not a territory for the unprepared, traveler.\n\nI suggest you be extremely careful if you venture outside the settlement.
It always gives me some comfort to see another warrior sent out to this gods-forsaken swamp.\n\nNever thought I'd miss the deserts of Brimstone Sands, but I certainly do.
Yes, this is exactly what I was hoping to find. Don't you see? \n\nThe Ancients forced their human subjects here to work on some type of… machinery.
Damn it, but I wish Abbington was here! Who knows? The old fool may have become Lost or Corrupted.\n\nWithout him, I'm afraid I have to continue to entrust you with this work.
One thing Is certain - the Ancients were not benevolent rulers.\n\nHowever horrific it is, the mystery of what powered the Hearts remains.
I have to tell you, though, the source of the Dryads' essence is not the real mystery here.\n\nIt's this azoth crystal - it is not natural, but rather… crafted somehow.
There may be one thing, however, that could redeem this entire initiative.\n\nAmong the tablets you gathered, I've seen reference to a place known as the Lazarus Well.
I cannot express what a difference you made. Without you, this entire effort would've been wasted.\n\nNow I will return to New Corsica with pride... and years of research cut out for me.
The marshes of this land are like no other in all Aeternum\n\nIn the Old World, it was life that made nature so spectactular. Here, it is death
Greetings and welcome to Reekwater, traveler. I hope you have not brought trouble with you.\n\nWe have trouble enough here already.
Ah, it's you, {playerName}. I am pleased you have returned.\n\nI have studied my journals and reminded myself of all things relevant to restoring harmony here.
Of course, necessary as it may have been, killing the Dryads in Fisher's Glory will be an offense to the Angry Earth.\n\nIf we mean to restore harmony, we will have to atone for that.
Now, I hope you'll help me resolve one other point of contention with Afolabi.\n\nShe insists the Dryads gathering here from across Aeternum is not to protect Reekwater.
Ah, yes… of course! There are legends about a place called the Eternal Pool.\n\nWith this drawing, we may finally have discovered the pool's location.
Thank you, {playerName}, for helping me finally learn the truth aboyt the Dryads… and myself.
This settlement is facing hard times. Traveler.\n\nYou are welcome here, but I cannot vouch for your safety.
What have we here? Someone finally comes to help us? The Legion came, but they do nothing. \n\nI have sounded the alarm in Reekwater for months, but no one understands the danger.

Now you can see. They spread like a plague, cobbling together flotsam into landlocked monstrosities. But you have found something more?\nThese notes… they were all penned by the same hand, one that has experienced the cruelty of the Siren Queen firsthand.\nYou must find her. We must know what she knows!
I know that her ambitions know no bounds, but I do not know what she truly seeks to achieve.\n\nIs it dominion over all Aeternum? How would that be satisying to one of the Lost?
Now, it all makes sense - her crew, my village, any other power she can draw - the Siren Queen wants to regain her soul.\n\nAnd it would seem to empower herself even further in the process.

Your efforts have been noticed by the Siren Queen, and she has deployed her trusted lieutenants to the front in an attempt to stall any attack.\nThe time for a direct confrontation is upon us, whether we wish it or not.
My old village cannot be avenged until the Siren Queen herself is defeated, for good.\n\nI also fear that every moment she may be finding other ways to increase her power.
Tread carefully in the swamps of Reekwater, wayfarer.\n\nNature is beautiful, but it is also quite treacherous.
Greetings, young one. I have seen you speaking with Herbalist Langlais.\n\nI believe you helped her retrieve her journals, yes? A kindness, indeed.
The question that remains to be answered is the Dryads' motivation for coming to Reekwater.\n\nIs it that they come to serve and protect the nature here, or another reason?
I have told you all I can for now, young one.\n\nSpeak to Herbalist Langlais, and I feel certain you will learn more together.
Greetings again, young one. You have been to the Eternal Pool and seen the truth.\n\nReekwater is the end of the cycle of life for the Dryads, but balance is still not restored.
If you see any artifacts in these ruins, hands off!\n\nI've already claimed anything in this place in the name of research. I'm not leaving, either.
This artifact, it's… well, it's a power no being should wield.\n\nAnd no matter what, we can't let it fall into Fulvius's hands!
Thank you for what you did out in those ruins.\n\nI promise you - I'm putting that relic somewhere the Legion will never find it.
Ah, Umbra's Reach. On anyone else's hand, it would actually give me cause for concern, but not so with you.\n\nWear it well, and in good faith, friend.
Shhh! Don't let them know I'm here.\n\nPlease, please… anything but that.
I mean, what was I to do? I didn't want to let her suck out my soul.\n\nSo I've been hiding here… like for a REALLY long time. Safer here than anywhere out there.

The thing you gotta get is that the Siren Queen may have lost her soul, but she's gained something else.\n\nI don't know what exactly, I mean this island's got all kinds of magics, and she's been scooping them up.
After that, she holed up in her cabin with the thing, and started inviting crew members in one-by-one.\n\nWhen they came out, they were Lost… mindlessly doing her bidding.
Come on now. We had a moment there, but it's not like we're friends.\n\nThis is my hiding spot - you go find your own.
I haven't the patience to entertain commoners. Begone.
Good health to you, Marauder. What is your request?
Good health to you, Marauder. What is your request?\n\n[ Level 56 required for Reekwater faction missions ]
Spare us both and move on, genius.
Save your good words. I need them not.
You were helplessly drawn to me, no?  You think it is my charisma?
It is your pleasure to conversate with me, yes? How might I satisfy your wants, my friend?
It is your pleasure to conversate with me, yes? How might I satisfy your wants, my friend?\n\n[ Level 56 required for Reekwater faction missions ]
Your primative mind is fascinated by me, right, Marauder? How could it not be so?
Do you find a crisis of faith in my eyes, devotee? Perhaps the doubt is now creeping in?
It is not safe in this land. The Covenant provides me protection and purpose. I suggest you seek the same.
May the Spark carry you. How may I assist you?
May the Spark carry you. How may I assist you?\n\n[ Level 56 required for Reekwater faction missions ]
Do not be so bold, warrior. This is land is perilous, especially for the foolhardy.
You seek knowledge. I have advice. Forget your experiments and leave Reekwater while you can.
Just in case you were wondering - all the drinks I serve are clean.\n\nI run all the water I use through six layers of cloth, then triple distill it. Purest water you ever drank.

Oi! Over here! Headman told me to keep an eye out for you, let you know if that Siren tart showed her scaly bum again.\nLooks like she and those barnacles she calls her 'crew' are back and trying to start trouble again.
Here is what I wish to know - why do they call this place Reekwater?\n\nIt's not like there is a bad odor… or is it just me?
You must be one with the fish, one with the waters… If you wish to be a Grand Master Fisher like me.
You must be one with the fish, one with the waters… If you wish to be a Grand Master Fisher like me.
Greetings, fellow Grand Master. What news do you bring?
Strangers. If you have come to serve you must cleanse yourself with imbued Azoth Water. Go now, to the bath chamber and return once you are done.
You've returned, but not all of you are cleansed. Return to me when all of you have completed this task.
You've returned, but not all of you are present. Return to me with all of the members of your group.
You've returned. I see you are cleansed. I still question your worth. Are you willing to risk all to prove your value?
